\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 1.       Aldrovanda}        L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By D.A. Webb.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Stems submerged, rootless. Leaves whorled. Flowers axillary; stamens 5; styles 5.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. A. vesiculosa} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 281 (1753). Leaves 10-15 mm, in crowded whorls of 6-9; each with a cuneate basal part, and terminating in 4-6 setaceous segments and an orbicular lobe, 1 hinged along the midrib, which can close rapidly to entrap and digest small animals. Flowers shortly pedicellate, rarely produced in Europe and usually cleistogamous. Petals 4-5 mm, greenish-white. Perennation by persistent terminal buds.{\i  Usually in shallow, still water. Dispersed irregularly and sparsely over a large part of Europe, mainly in the centre and east; declining over much of its European range}. †Au †Bu Cz Ga Ge He Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs(C, W, E).
