\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 2.       Drosera}           L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By D.A. Webb.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Small plants of wet places. Leaves all basal; upper surface of lamina covered with long, red, gland-tipped, motile hairs, which entrap and digest insects. Scape slender, bearing a slender, spike-like, ebracteate cyme. Flowers usually 5-merous, sometimes 4- or 6-8 merous, open for a short time only, sometimes cleistogamous. Petals white; stamens equal in number to the petals. Carpels usually 3; styles free, deeply bifid.
\par

